search::createQuery()

Description
    private string search::createQuery(string $searchType, array $keywords)
    Creates a valid MySQL query.

Parameters
    keywords
    An array containing one or more instances of "and", "not", or "*".

Return Values
    Returns a string containing a MySQL query.

Examples
    <?php
	...
	foreach ($this->searchArray as $searchType => $keywords) {

	    $sql = $this->createQuery($searchType,$keywords);
	    if (debugNeeded("query")) {
		print "<br />".htmlSanitize($sql)."<br /><br />";
	    }

	    $this->engine->openDB->sanitize = FALSE;
	    $sqlResult = $this->engine->openDB->query($sql);
	    $results[] = $sqlResult['result'];
	}
	...
    ?>

Notes
    $searchType isn't actually used in this function.
   
See Also
    search::buildWhereClause()
    search::buildQuery()
